I'll re-consider.
At some point I realized that I've added this line of code to too many specialization classes of PanelAbstract. I think it should be better with a check like:

```
if (PackageResource.exists(klass, klass.getSimpleName() + ".css")) {
  PanelUtil.renderHead(response, klass);
}
```

This way there won't be empty (licence only) `.css` files around.
